moves.name: Protect
moves.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

moves.name: Will-O-Wisp
moves.desc: Burns the target.
moves.shortDesc: Burns the target.

moves.name: Iron Defense
moves.desc: Raises the user's Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Defense by 2.

moves.name: Body Press
moves.desc: Damage is calculated using the user's Defense stat as its Attack, including stat stage changes. Other effects that modify the Attack stat are used as normal.
moves.shortDesc: Uses user's Def stat as Atk in damage calculation.

moves.name: Rock Slide
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to make the foe(s) flinch.

moves.name: Earthquake
moves.desc: Damage doubles if the target is using Dig.
moves.shortDesc: Hits adjacent Pokemon. Double damage on Dig.

moves.name: Heat Crash
moves.desc: The power of this move depends on (user's weight / target's weight), rounded down. Power is equal to 120 if the result is 5 or more, 100 if 4, 80 if 3, 60 if 2, and 40 if 1 or less. Damage doubles and no accuracy check is done if the target has used Minimize while active.
moves.shortDesc: More power the heavier the user than the target.

moves.name: Heat Wave
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to burn the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to burn the foe(s).

moves.name: Power Gem
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Earth Power
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Endure
moves.desc: The user will survive attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn with at least 1 HP. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: User survives attacks this turn with at least 1 HP.

moves.name: Flare Blitz
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to burn the target. If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 33% the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
moves.shortDesc: Has 33% recoil. 10% chance to burn. Thaws user.

moves.name: Scald
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to burn the target. The target thaws out if it is frozen.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to burn the target. Thaws target.

moves.name: Scorching Sands
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to burn the target. The target thaws out if it is frozen.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to burn the target. Thaws target.

moves.name: Explosion
moves.desc: The user faints after using this move, even if this move fails for having no target. This move is prevented from executing if any active Pokemon has the Damp Ability.
moves.shortDesc: Hits adjacent Pokemon. The user faints.

moves.name: Meteor Beam
moves.desc: This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. Raises the user's Special Attack by 1 stage on the first turn. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
moves.shortDesc: Raises user's Sp. Atk by 1 on turn 1. Hits turn 2.

moves.name: Tera Blast
moves.desc: If the user is Terastallized, this move becomes a physical attack if the user's Attack is greater than its Special Attack, including stat stage changes, and this move's type becomes the same as the user's Tera Type. In addition, if the user's Tera Type is Stellar, this move has 100 power, is super effective against Terastallized targets and neutral against other targets, and lowers the user's Attack and Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: If Terastallized: Phys. if Atk > SpA, type = Tera.

moves.name: Heavy Slam
moves.desc: The power of this move depends on (user's weight / target's weight), rounded down. Power is equal to 120 if the result is 5 or more, 100 if 4, 80 if 3, 60 if 2, and 40 if 1 or less. Damage doubles and no accuracy check is done if the target has used Minimize while active.
moves.shortDesc: More power the heavier the user than the target.

moves.name: Ancient Power
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to raise the user's Attack, Defense, Special Attack, Special Defense, and Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to raise all stats by 1 (not acc/eva).

moves.name: Solar Beam
moves.desc: This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. Power is halved if the weather is Primordial Sea, Rain Dance, Sandstorm, or Snow and the user is not holding Utility Umbrella. If the user is holding a Power Herb or the weather is Desolate Land or Sunny Day, the move completes in one turn. If the user is holding Utility Umbrella and the weather is Desolate Land or Sunny Day, the move still requires a turn to charge.
moves.shortDesc: Charges turn 1. Hits turn 2. No charge in sunlight.

moves.name: Iron Head
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to make the target flinch.

moves.name: Flamethrower
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to burn the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to burn the target.

moves.name: High Horsepower
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Rock Blast
moves.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 35% chance to hit two or three times and a 15% chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times.
moves.shortDesc: Hits 2-5 times in one turn.

moves.name: Rapid Spin
moves.desc: If this move is successful and the user has not fainted, the effects of Leech Seed and binding moves end for the user, and all hazards are removed from the user's side of the field. Has a 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Free user from hazards/bind/Leech Seed; +1 Spe.

moves.name: Spikes
moves.desc: Sets up a hazard on the opposing side of the field, damaging each opposing Pokemon that switches in, unless it is a Flying-type Pokemon or has the Levitate Ability. Can be used up to three times before failing. Opponents lose 1/8 of their maximum HP with one layer, 1/6 of their maximum HP with two layers, and 1/4 of their maximum HP with three layers, all rounded down. Can be removed from the opposing side if any opposing Pokemon uses Mortal Spin, Rapid Spin, or Defog successfully, or is hit by Defog.
moves.shortDesc: Hurts grounded foes on switch-in. Max 3 layers.

moves.name: Tar Shot
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Speed by 1 stage. Until the target switches out, the effectiveness of Fire-type moves is doubled against it.
moves.shortDesc: Target gets -1 Spe and becomes weaker to Fire.

moves.name: Fire Punch
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to burn the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to burn the target.

moves.name: Gyro Ball
moves.desc: Power is equal to (25 * target's current Speed / user's current Speed) + 1, rounded down, but not more than 150. If the user's current Speed is 0, this move's power is 1.
moves.shortDesc: More power the slower the user than the target.

moves.name: Sleep Talk
moves.desc: One of the user's known moves, besides this move, is selected for use at random. Fails if the user is not asleep. The selected move does not have PP deducted from it, and can currently have 0 PP. This move cannot select Assist, Beak Blast, Belch, Bide, Blazing Torque, Celebrate, Chatter, Combat Torque, Copycat, Dynamax Cannon, Focus Punch, Hold Hands, Magical Torque, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Move, Nature Power, Noxious Torque, Shell Trap, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Struggle, Uproar, Wicked Torque, or any two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: User must be asleep. Uses another known move.

moves.name: Stealth Rock
moves.desc: Sets up a hazard on the opposing side of the field, damaging each opposing Pokemon that switches in. Fails if the effect is already active on the opposing side. Foes lose 1/32, 1/16, 1/8, 1/4, or 1/2 of their maximum HP, rounded down, based on their weakness to the Rock type; 0.25x, 0.5x, neutral, 2x, or 4x, respectively. Can be removed from the opposing side if any opposing Pokemon uses Mortal Spin, Rapid Spin, or Defog successfully, or is hit by Defog.
moves.shortDesc: Hurts foes on switch-in. Factors Rock weakness.

moves.name: Sunny Day
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Sunny Day. The damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Heat Rock. Fails if the current weather is Sunny Day.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, intense sunlight powers Fire moves.

moves.name: Fire Blast
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to burn the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to burn the target.

moves.name: Temper Flare
moves.desc: Power doubles if the user's last move on the previous turn, including moves called by other moves or those used through Instruct, Magic Coat, Snatch, or the Dancer or Magic Bounce Abilities, failed to do any of its normal effects, not including damage from an unsuccessful High Jump Kick, Jump Kick, or Mind Blown, or if the user was prevented from moving by any effect other than recharging or Sky Drop. A move that was blocked by Baneful Bunker, Detect, King's Shield, Protect, Spiky Shield, Crafty Shield, Mat Block, Quick Guard, or Wide Guard will not double this move's power, nor will Bounce or Fly ending early due to the effect of Gravity, Smack Down, or Thousand Arrows.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if the user's last move failed.

moves.name: Sandstorm
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Sandstorm. At the end of each turn except the last, all active Pokemon lose 1/16 of their maximum HP, rounded down, unless they are a Ground, Rock, or Steel type, or have the Magic Guard, Overcoat, Sand Force, Sand Rush, or Sand Veil Abilities. During the effect, the Special Defense of Rock-type Pokemon is multiplied by 1.5 when taking damage from a special attack. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Smooth Rock. Fails if the current weather is Sandstorm.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, a sandstorm rages. Rock: 1.5x SpD.

moves.name: Reflect
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 0.5x damage from physical attacks, or 0.66x damage if in a Double Battle. Damage is not reduced further with Aurora Veil. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break, Psychic Fangs, or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, physical damage to allies is halved.

moves.name: Bulldoze
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance lower adjacent Pkmn Speed by 1.

moves.name: Rest
moves.desc: The user falls asleep for the next two turns and restores all of its HP, curing itself of any non-volatile status condition in the process. Fails if the user has full HP, is already asleep, or if another effect is preventing sleep.
moves.shortDesc: User sleeps 2 turns and restores HP and status.

moves.name: Overheat
moves.desc: Lowers the user's Special Attack by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the user's Sp. Atk by 2.

moves.name: Flame Charge
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1.

moves.name: Body Slam
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target. Damage doubles and no accuracy check is done if the target has used Minimize while active.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to paralyze the target.

moves.name: Fire Spin
moves.desc: Prevents the target from switching for four or five turns (seven turns if the user is holding Grip Claw). Causes damage to the target equal to 1/8 of its maximum HP (1/6 if the user is holding Binding Band), rounded down, at the end of each turn during effect. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass, Flip Turn, Parting Shot, Shed Tail, Teleport, U-turn, or Volt Switch. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field, or if the target uses Mortal Spin, Rapid Spin, or Substitute successfully. This effect is not stackable or reset by using this or another binding move.
moves.shortDesc: Traps and damages the target for 4-5 turns.

moves.name: Smokescreen
moves.desc: Lowers the target's accuracy by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's accuracy by 1.

moves.name: Substitute
moves.desc: The user takes 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and puts it into a substitute to take its place in battle. The substitute is removed once enough damage is inflicted on it, or if the user switches out or faints. Baton Pass can be used to transfer the substitute to an ally, and the substitute will keep its remaining HP. Until the substitute is broken, it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokemon and shields the user from status effects and stat stage changes caused by other Pokemon. Sound-based moves and Pokemon with the Infiltrator Ability ignore substitutes. The user still takes normal damage from weather and status effects while behind its substitute. If the substitute breaks during a multi-hit attack, the user will take damage from any remaining hits. If a substitute is created while the user is trapped by a binding move, the binding effect ends immediately. Fails if the user does not have enough HP remaining to create a substitute without fainting, or if it already has a substitute.
moves.shortDesc: User takes 1/4 its max HP to put in a substitute.

moves.name: Rock Polish
moves.desc: Raises the user's Speed by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Speed by 2.

moves.name: Facade
moves.desc: Power doubles if the user is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned. The physical damage halving effect from the user's burn is ignored.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is burn/poison/paralyzed.

moves.name: Curse
moves.desc: If the user is not a Ghost type, lowers the user's Speed by 1 stage and raises the user's Attack and Defense by 1 stage. If the user is a Ghost type, the user loses 1/2 of its maximum HP, rounded down and even if it would cause fainting, in exchange for the target losing 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn while it is active. If the target uses Baton Pass, the replacement will continue to be affected. Fails if there is no target or if the target is already affected.
moves.shortDesc: Curses if Ghost, else -1 Spe, +1 Atk, +1 Def.

moves.name: Incinerate
moves.desc: The target loses its held item if it is a Berry or a Gem. This move cannot cause Pokemon with the Sticky Hold Ability to lose their held item. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
moves.shortDesc: Destroys the foe(s) Berry/Gem.

moves.name: Rock Tomb
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1.

abilities.name: Flash Fire
abilities.desc: This Pokemon is immune to Fire-type moves. The first time it is hit by a Fire-type move, its offensive stat is multiplied by 1.5 while using a Fire-type attack as long as it remains active and has this Ability. If this Pokemon is frozen, it cannot be defrosted by Fire-type attacks.
abilities.shortDesc: This Pokemon's Fire attacks do 1.5x damage if hit by one Fire move; Fire immunity.

abilities.name: Steam Engine
abilities.desc: This Pokemon's Speed is raised by 6 stages after it is damaged by a Fire- or Water-type move.
abilities.shortDesc: This Pokemon's Speed is raised by 6 stages after it is damaged by Fire/Water moves.

abilities.name: Flame Body
abilities.desc: 30% chance a Pokemon making contact with this Pokemon will be burned.
abilities.shortDesc: 30% chance a Pokemon making contact with this Pokemon will be burned.

items.name: Air Balloon

items.name: Assault Vest
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Def is 1.5x, but it can only select damaging moves.

items.name: Absorb Bulb
items.desc: Raises holder's Sp. Atk by 1 stage if hit by a Water-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Power Herb

items.name: Expert Belt

items.name: Passho Berry

items.name: Miracle Seed
items.desc: Holder's Grass-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Choice Specs
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Atk is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Choice Band
items.desc: Holder's Attack is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Focus Sash
items.desc: If holder's HP is full, will survive an attack that would KO it with 1 HP. Single use.

items.name: Loaded Dice
items.desc: Holder's moves that hit 2-5 times hit 4-5 times; Population Bomb hits 4-10 times.

items.name: Covert Cloak
items.desc: Holder is not affected by the secondary effect of another Pokemon's attack.

items.name: Clear Amulet
items.desc: Prevents other Pokemon from lowering the holder's stat stages.

items.name: Charcoal
items.desc: Holder's Fire-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Sitrus Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/4 max HP when at 1/2 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Iapapa Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Def Nature. Single use.

items.name: Occa Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Fire-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Mago Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Spe Nature. Single use.

items.name: Wiki Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpA Nature. Single use.

items.name: Heavy-Duty Boots
items.desc: When switching in, the holder is unaffected by hazards on its side of the field.

items.name: Heat Rock
items.desc: Holder's use of Sunny Day lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Mental Herb
items.desc: Cures holder of Attract, Disable, Encore, Heal Block, Taunt, Torment. Single use.

items.name: Life Orb
items.desc: Holder's attacks do 1.3x damage, and it loses 1/10 its max HP after the attack.

items.name: Safety Goggles
items.desc: Holder is immune to powder moves and damage from Sandstorm or Hail.

items.name: Figy Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Atk Nature. Single use.

items.name: King's Rock
items.desc: Holder's attacks without a chance to make the target flinch gain a 10% chance to make the target flinch. Evolves Poliwhirl into Politoed and Slowpoke into Slowking when traded.

items.name: Wide Lens
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks by the holder is 1.1x.

items.name: Quick Claw
items.desc: Each turn, holder has a 20% chance to move first in its priority bracket.

items.name: Wise Glasses
items.desc: Holder's special attacks have 1.1x power.

items.name: Maranga Berry
items.desc: Raises holder's Sp. Def by 1 stage after it is hit by a special attack. Single use.

items.name: Luminous Moss
items.desc: Raises holder's Sp. Def by 1 stage if hit by a Water-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Shell Bell
items.desc: After an attack, holder gains 1/8 of the damage in HP dealt to other Pokemon.
